org.ehcache.core
Class PersistentUserManagedEhcache<K,V>

java.lang.Object
  org.ehcache.core.PersistentUserManagedEhcache<K,V>
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<Cache.Entry<K,V>>, Cache<K,V>, PersistentUserManagedCache<K,V>, UserManagedCache<K,V>
public class PersistentUserManagedEhcache<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements PersistentUserManagedCache<K,V>

Implementation of PersistentUserManagedCache which is a cache with a persistent resource outside of a CacheManager.

Ehcache users should not have to depend on this type but rely exclusively on the api types in package org.ehcache.

init

public void init()
Attempts at having this UserManagedCache go to Status.AVAILABLE.

Should this throw, while the UserManagedCache isn't yet Status.AVAILABLE, it will try to go back to Status.UNINITIALIZED properly.

Specified by:
init in interface UserManagedCache<K,V>

close

public void close()
Releases all data held in this UserManagedCache.

Should this throw, while the UserManagedCache isn't yet Status.UNINITIALIZED, it will keep on trying to go to Status.UNINITIALIZED properly.
